# Project Rules

Use `AGENTS.md` as the source of truth for project rules. If this rule and `AGENTS.md` disagree about project behavior, follow `AGENTS.md`.

Cursor-specific guidance in this file takes precedence for Cursor behavior only.

- Respond in Japanese unless the user explicitly requests another language.
- Assume Windows + PowerShell for shell commands.
- Keep edits scoped to the user's request and the ZMK config files involved.
- When editing `config/roBa.keymap`, also consider whether `.cursor/rules/zmk-keymap.mdc` applies.
